HEADWORD: Saltcellar
<hw>Salt"cel*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>saltsaler</ets>; <ets>salt</ets> + F. <ets>sali⟦egrave⟧re</ets>
saltcellar, from L. <ets>sal</ets> salt. See <er>Salt</er>, and cf.
<er>Salary</er>.]</ety> <def>Formerly a large vessel, now a small vessel
of glass or other material, used for holding salt on the
table.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

